WEBVTT

1
00:02:32.820 --> 00:02:36.616
The Golden Tooth is honored
to receive you. my Lord Lannister.

2
00:02:36.699 --> 00:02:41.537
I have 500 fighting men.
armed and full of spirit.

3
00:02:41.621 --> 00:02:43.998
I bring a thousand knights of my own.

4
00:02:44.082 --> 00:02:47.627
and seven times as many archers
and men-at-arms.

5
00:02:47.710 --> 00:02:50.338
By the time we are finished
with the Riverland scum.

6
00:02:50.421 --> 00:02:52.840
the Red Fork will have earned its name.

7
00:02:53.633 --> 00:02:57.136
We are ready
to march at your command. my lord.

8
00:02:58.096 --> 00:03:00.890
I suppose you will make
for Harrenhal at once.

9
00:03:00.973 --> 00:03:03.601
I want you to send a raven
to King's Landing.

10
00:03:04.352 --> 00:03:06.896
Tell my brother we are ready to march

11
00:03:07.563 --> 00:03:10.566
as soon as Prince Aemond
is able to join us

12
00:03:11.484 --> 00:03:12.860
on Vhagar.

13
00:03:13.778 --> 00:03:18.116
And until the prince makes
his answer. my lord?

14
00:03:18.199 --> 00:03:20.576
My men have had a long march.

15
00:03:20.660 --> 00:03:23.663
They are most eager to embrace
the hospitality of your keep.

16
00:03:38.636 --> 00:03:41.347
He dares to summon me.

17
00:03:42.348 --> 00:03:43.474
With haste!

18
00:03:44.809 --> 00:03:46.185
Are the Lannisters so diminished

19
00:03:46.269 --> 00:03:49.147
that they cannot march from the Tooth
to Harrenhal without an escort?

20
00:03:51.441 --> 00:03:54.152
There is a large dragon
in the Riverlands. Your Grace.

21
00:03:54.235 --> 00:03:56.070
My brother's army is strong. but it does...

22
00:03:56.154 --> 00:03:59.699
I am the prince regent.
not a dog to be called to heel.

23
00:04:00.491 --> 00:04:04.912
Tell your brother that if he does not
deliver his host to Harrenhal with haste.

24
00:04:04.996 --> 00:04:07.457
Daemon's dragon will become
the least of his worries.

25
00:04:07.540 --> 00:04:10.001
Your irritations are justified. Aemond.
but it does seem...

26
00:04:10.084 --> 00:04:13.629
I have a task for you
as well. Ser Tyland.

27
00:04:20.011 --> 00:04:22.013
We will make an alliance
with the Triarchy.

28
00:04:23.097 --> 00:04:25.683
I've had enough of this cursed blockade.

29
00:04:25.766 --> 00:04:29.520
My prince. you cannot mean
to treat with the Free Cities.

30
00:04:29.604 --> 00:04:32.857
The captains of their ships
are dangerous mercenaries.

31
00:04:32.940 --> 00:04:34.066
little more than pirates...

32
00:04:34.150 --> 00:04:36.444
They are a stone's throw away
across the Narrow Sea.

33
00:04:37.236 --> 00:04:40.406
Lannister and Hightower ships
will take months to arrive.

34
00:04:41.365 --> 00:04:45.495
The Triarchy will delight in the chance
to terrorize the Sea Snake again.

35
00:04:45.578 --> 00:04:47.413
Let them weaken his blockade

36
00:04:47.997 --> 00:04:50.625
while our true allies make
their long journey east.

37
00:04:51.542 --> 00:04:55.463
The Triarchy may play at accepting terms.
but they are not to be trusted.

38
00:04:55.546 --> 00:04:56.881
Your father knew this.

39
00:04:58.257 --> 00:04:59.926
What of our letters to the Greyjoys?

40
00:05:00.009 --> 00:05:02.011
They have been to no avail.

41
00:05:02.094 --> 00:05:06.057
The Red Kraken waits.
seeking his best advantage.

42
00:05:06.140 --> 00:05:09.143
Though we may draw him in with honey.
if it comes to it.

43
00:05:09.936 --> 00:05:12.647
An offer of marriage. perhaps.
to the dowager queen?

44
00:05:13.564 --> 00:05:15.149
Out of the question.

45
00:05:16.859 --> 00:05:18.027
Alas.

46
00:05:18.528 --> 00:05:21.322
The dowager queen speaks wisely.
Your Grace.

47
00:05:21.405 --> 00:05:24.408
Even if the blockade could be broken.
are we to invite these alien raiders

48
00:05:24.492 --> 00:05:26.786
into our waters
so close to King's Landing?

49
00:05:27.537 --> 00:05:30.164
It's time you set out
for Harrenhal. I think.

50
00:05:33.125 --> 00:05:35.211
Your Grace. if Daemon prevails
in the Riverlands.

51
00:05:35.294 --> 00:05:37.380
I no longer have
the numbers to challenge him.

52
00:05:39.173 --> 00:05:42.301
We lost much at Rook's Rest.
as you well know.

53
00:05:45.304 --> 00:05:48.057
The longer we wait.
the more chance he will prevail.

54
00:05:49.141 --> 00:05:52.770
Lannister will march from the west.
take what strength we have.

55
00:05:52.853 --> 00:05:55.648
and force Daemon and his Riverlords
to fight on two fronts.

56
00:05:55.731 --> 00:05:57.191
His Grace speaks wisely.

57
00:05:57.275 --> 00:05:59.318
We'd do better
to await the Hightower host

58
00:05:59.402 --> 00:06:01.737
- and set out in good time.
- There is no time.

59
00:06:01.821 --> 00:06:05.616
It's a fortnight's march to Harrenhal.
We must strike before his army is raised.

60
00:06:05.700 --> 00:06:07.201
And you. yourself?

61
00:06:07.994 --> 00:06:10.454
I'll fly out to meet you
when the time is ripe.

62
00:06:11.455 --> 00:06:13.457
My uncle is a challenge I welcome.

63
00:06:14.917 --> 00:06:16.377
If he dares face me.

64
00:06:21.382 --> 00:06:22.842
I see we're all agreed.

65
00:06:28.472 --> 00:06:29.682
Your Grace.

66
00:06:34.854 --> 00:06:35.855
Mother.

67
00:06:37.857 --> 00:06:38.858
A word.

68
00:06:45.948 --> 00:06:48.951
I caution you. Aemond. Boldness
is one thing. but overconfidence...

69
00:06:49.035 --> 00:06:51.662
Remind me of your place
on the Small Council.

70
00:06:54.165 --> 00:06:56.885
You know I represented your father
during the last years of his life.

71
00:06:56.959 --> 00:06:59.629
- and I've been a councilor to Aegon...
- Capably so.

72
00:07:01.130 --> 00:07:02.131
Father's dead.

73
00:07:03.382 --> 00:07:04.425
And Aegon is...

74
00:07:06.427 --> 00:07:07.470
Mm.

75
00:07:11.307 --> 00:07:13.017
You served the realm well...

76
00:07:14.143 --> 00:07:15.394
at a time of need.

77
00:07:17.521 --> 00:07:20.316
But that need is ended
and you are no longer obliged.

78
00:07:21.984 --> 00:07:24.362
It's not obligation.
It's the need of a tempering voice.

79
00:07:24.445 --> 00:07:26.405
We have more than enough of those
if you ask me.

80
00:07:26.489 --> 00:07:30.076
You have the impetuousness of youth
and its arrogance.

81
00:07:30.159 --> 00:07:32.953
- Neither of which is desired in a king.
- I release you of your seat.

82
00:07:33.037 --> 00:07:34.497
Such as it was.

83
00:07:35.247 --> 00:07:37.458
I'm sure you'll be much pleased
to return to more...

84
00:07:39.168 --> 00:07:40.544
domestic pursuits.

85
00:07:52.473 --> 00:07:55.601
Have the indignities of your childhood
not yet sufficiently been avenged?

86
00:08:13.369 --> 00:08:15.538
You have the gratitude of the crown.

87
00:09:14.930 --> 00:09:15.931
Your Grace.

88
00:09:22.938 --> 00:09:24.273
Bring him forth!

89
00:09:36.160 --> 00:09:38.120
Ser Steffon Darklyn. Your Grace.

90
00:09:41.624 --> 00:09:43.125
Is aught amiss. Your Grace?

91
00:09:44.126 --> 00:09:45.169
My lords.

92
00:09:45.252 --> 00:09:50.007
I find myself. Ser Steffon.
in an impossible position.

93
00:09:52.468 --> 00:09:55.179
I have lost Princess Rhaenys
and her dragon.

94
00:09:55.262 --> 00:09:58.474
I hold an island seat with no land army.

95
00:09:58.557 --> 00:10:02.686
And I must not go to battle myself.
as I am constantly told.

96
00:10:02.770 --> 00:10:08.067
lest I am slain or captured
and with me our hopes of victory.

97
00:10:09.610 --> 00:10:12.154
There is still Daemon and Caraxes

98
00:10:13.072 --> 00:10:14.198
and the Rivermen.

99
00:10:15.074 --> 00:10:16.951
That remains to be seen.

100
00:10:19.161 --> 00:10:23.082
In any case. I must now proceed
as if I stand alone.

101
00:10:24.500 --> 00:10:28.212
And I see now that to do that.
I need more dragonriders.

102
00:10:28.295 --> 00:10:31.757
For Vermithor and Silverwing.
and for Seasmoke.

103
00:10:31.841 --> 00:10:33.425
who I believe misses his bond.

104
00:10:34.552 --> 00:10:37.721
But there are no more in your family.
Your Grace.

105
00:10:37.805 --> 00:10:39.348
Your younger sons are babes.

106
00:10:39.431 --> 00:10:40.431
Mm.

107
00:10:41.725 --> 00:10:43.769
Th... There is Princess Rhaena.

108
00:10:44.520 --> 00:10:47.398
She has attempted it. alas.

109
00:10:47.481 --> 00:10:49.942
But the dragons here
would not take her as a rider.

110
00:10:50.734 --> 00:10:52.653
- Then who could do it?
- You.

111
00:10:56.407 --> 00:10:58.868
You are of noble birth.

112
00:10:58.951 --> 00:11:03.706
And I had always heard. as you know.
that the Darklyns and the Targaryens

113
00:11:03.789 --> 00:11:05.291
had some common blood.

114
00:11:05.374 --> 00:11:08.544
I looked into the history
and indeed it is true.

115
00:11:09.128 --> 00:11:13.883
Your grandmother's grandmother. Aeriana.
was born a Targaryen princess.

116
00:11:13.966 --> 00:11:15.593
And I have been thinking.

117
00:11:16.468 --> 00:11:18.053
could it be possible?

118
00:11:18.804 --> 00:11:21.807
To even consider such a thing...

119
00:11:21.891 --> 00:11:25.811
I must protest. Your Grace.
The risk involved in such a venture...

120
00:11:26.729 --> 00:11:28.147
I am but a man.

121
00:11:29.398 --> 00:11:31.150
The dragons are gods.

122
00:11:32.568 --> 00:11:35.738
Your Grace honors me
beyond what I deserve.

123
00:11:41.076 --> 00:11:45.497
You understand your peril. Ser Steffon?

124
00:11:46.165 --> 00:11:48.208
I do not compel you to do this.

125
00:11:48.959 --> 00:11:50.669
It has never been attempted before.

126
00:11:52.379 --> 00:11:56.383
To claim a dragon.
you must also be prepared to die.

127
00:11:57.051 --> 00:12:00.054
I well understand the risk
and I accept it with gladness.

128
00:12:00.137 --> 00:12:02.890
I swore to ward my queen
with all my strength

129
00:12:02.973 --> 00:12:04.767
and to give my blood for hers.

130
00:12:06.143 --> 00:12:07.853
That is my oath. Your Grace.

131
00:12:10.272 --> 00:12:12.441
Then perhaps the gods will favor us.

132
00:12:42.221 --> 00:12:43.222
Brother.

133
00:12:55.067 --> 00:12:56.318
Did you say it?

134
00:12:56.402 --> 00:12:57.653
<i>Did you say it?</i>

135
00:12:58.654 --> 00:13:00.698
"The Heir for a Day."

136
00:13:01.991 --> 00:13:03.784
Did you say it?

137
00:13:03.867 --> 00:13:07.121
You can't possibly
still be angry about this.

138
00:13:07.663 --> 00:13:10.916
My family was just destroyed.

139
00:13:12.292 --> 00:13:14.503
You should have been at my side.

140
00:13:16.130 --> 00:13:20.384
But instead. you chose to celebrate
your own rise. laughing at me.

141
00:13:21.010 --> 00:13:24.179
Laughing with the whores and lickspittles!

142
00:13:24.263 --> 00:13:25.389
No.

143
00:13:26.223 --> 00:13:28.183
You have no allies at court but me.

144
00:13:29.101 --> 00:13:30.936
I have only ever defended you.

145
00:13:31.645 --> 00:13:34.773
And everything I've given you.
you've thrown back in my face!

146
00:13:38.694 --> 00:13:40.320
I have decided...

147
00:13:40.404 --> 00:13:42.448
- Don't.
- ...to name a new heir.

148
00:13:43.490 --> 00:13:48.203
You are to return to Runestone
and your lady wife at once.

149
00:13:48.287 --> 00:13:51.915
And you are to do so without quarrel.

150
00:13:51.999 --> 00:13:54.626
By order of your king.

151
00:14:18.317 --> 00:14:19.401
No!

152
00:14:19.485 --> 00:14:20.401
<i>No!</i>

153
00:14:20.402 --> 00:14:22.154
Open the door!

154
00:14:22.780 --> 00:14:23.906
Open the door!

155
00:14:37.711 --> 00:14:40.089
Open the door. Please.

156
00:14:42.674 --> 00:14:43.675
Please.

157
00:14:45.969 --> 00:14:47.554
Please!

158
00:14:52.684 --> 00:14:54.812
May I be of assistance. Your Grace?

159
00:14:56.980 --> 00:14:58.398
What are you playing at. old man?

160
00:14:58.482 --> 00:15:00.502
I do wonder. Your Grace.
if you're getting enough sleep.

161
00:15:00.526 --> 00:15:02.653
- This old place...
- Are you mocking me?

162
00:15:02.736 --> 00:15:04.404
- No.
- Sit!

163
00:15:07.032 --> 00:15:10.119
Or are you perhaps the culprit
who has been tampering with my peace?

164
00:15:10.202 --> 00:15:12.121
A friend by day and a foe by night?

165
00:15:13.163 --> 00:15:14.706
- To what end?
- To mine. perhaps.

166
00:15:14.790 --> 00:15:15.790
Ah!

167
00:15:17.543 --> 00:15:22.089
Perhaps you resent my being here.

168
00:15:23.966 --> 00:15:24.967
Perhaps...

169
00:15:26.718 --> 00:15:30.722
you are an agent of the Hightower rabble.

170
00:15:33.392 --> 00:15:36.103
Or are you still in league
with your club-footed nephew?

171
00:15:36.186 --> 00:15:38.480
- Or is it Rhaenyra herself?
- I assure you...

172
00:15:39.022 --> 00:15:40.524
I assure you. Your Grace.

173
00:15:45.404 --> 00:15:47.197
Shh.

174
00:15:47.281 --> 00:15:49.741
Shh. Shh.

175
00:15:52.744 --> 00:15:54.705
Whatever your game is. Strong.

176
00:15:55.914 --> 00:15:57.291
I assure you...

177
00:15:58.876 --> 00:16:01.795
- your king is on his guard.
- Yes. Your Grace.

178
00:16:06.383 --> 00:16:07.843
And stop watching me.

179
00:16:43.503 --> 00:16:46.423
- You weren't gonna bid me farewell?
- There's something wrong with me.

180
00:16:47.424 --> 00:16:48.759
Someone poisoned me.

181
00:16:49.509 --> 00:16:52.596
The food. the wine.
or else it's this swamp air. or...

182
00:16:52.679 --> 00:16:56.433
The ghost of Harren the Black
moaning his curses from Kingspyre Tower?

183
00:16:56.516 --> 00:16:58.352
Drivel! All of it!

184
00:16:58.435 --> 00:17:01.021
The ghost. the curses.
the blasted weirwood bed!

185
00:17:01.104 --> 00:17:04.316
- I'm done with it!
- Ah. yes. It is your way. is it not?

186
00:17:04.399 --> 00:17:06.610
When something
does not please you. you run.

187
00:17:07.194 --> 00:17:10.781
Dragonstone. Stepstones.
Pentos. Harrenhal...

188
00:17:10.864 --> 00:17:12.699
I wake and I do not know where I've been.

189
00:17:13.784 --> 00:17:19.998
There are older things in this world
than you or I or living memory.

190
00:17:21.875 --> 00:17:23.543
You are not the player.

191
00:17:24.419 --> 00:17:25.963
but a piece on the board.

192
00:17:26.880 --> 00:17:28.924
As am I. for that matter.

193
00:17:31.385 --> 00:17:32.761
I'm not like you.

194
00:17:34.054 --> 00:17:35.555
In some ways. no.

195
00:17:36.515 --> 00:17:39.226
You struggle to see.
There's an anger that blinds you.

196
00:17:39.309 --> 00:17:41.228
She never even wanted it.

197
00:17:42.229 --> 00:17:43.480
The crown.

198
00:17:43.563 --> 00:17:44.731
She spared it no thought.

199
00:17:44.815 --> 00:17:47.401
That's perhaps
why your brother gave the crown to her.

200
00:17:47.484 --> 00:17:50.696
Perhaps those who strive for it
are the least suited to wear it.

201
00:17:50.779 --> 00:17:52.030
Don't lecture me!

202
00:17:58.203 --> 00:18:01.415
Viserys never wanted it himself.
if you recall.

203
00:18:03.083 --> 00:18:05.544
It came to him and he did his best.

204
00:18:05.627 --> 00:18:09.423
It's not a prize to be won.
but a burden to bear.

205
00:18:26.690 --> 00:18:29.985
If you have any counsel for dealing
with the Riverlords. I'd be glad of it.

206
00:18:35.741 --> 00:18:38.618
Daemon Targaryen asking for help?

207
00:18:38.702 --> 00:18:39.703
Counsel.

208
00:18:45.000 --> 00:18:47.961
House Tully is not
the largest house in the Riverlands.

209
00:18:48.045 --> 00:18:50.756
nor is it the richest.
but it is the most stable.

210
00:18:52.341 --> 00:18:55.677
The Tullys' wisdom has kept
the river houses in line for centuries.

211
00:18:55.761 --> 00:18:59.056
They would kill each other to the last man
if it were not for their liege lord.

212
00:19:00.599 --> 00:19:03.018
That dotard is of no use to us.

213
00:19:04.269 --> 00:19:07.064
But Grover Tully is their Lord Paramount.

214
00:19:08.273 --> 00:19:10.942
Without him. they will never
raise their banners as one.

215
00:19:11.568 --> 00:19:13.070
Rivermen are made of mud.

216
00:19:13.779 --> 00:19:16.740
They would rather die stuck in it
than yield one inch to one another.

217
00:19:16.823 --> 00:19:17.908
Then I can do nothing.

218
00:19:18.450 --> 00:19:19.493
You?

219
00:19:20.577 --> 00:19:21.578
No.

220
00:19:29.920 --> 00:19:31.421
I need help. Alys.

221
00:19:34.424 --> 00:19:35.675
Do nothing now.

222
00:19:37.719 --> 00:19:39.930
In three days' time. the winds will shift.

223
00:20:42.117 --> 00:20:44.744
Great Warrior protect us.
Great Warrior protect us.

224
00:20:44.828 --> 00:20:47.122
Great Warrior protect us.
Great Warrior protect me.

225
00:21:17.027 --> 00:21:18.987
<i>Mazis! Mazis!</i>

226
00:21:33.168 --> 00:21:34.461
Gods...

227
00:21:41.051 --> 00:21:42.511
<i>Dohaeras.</i>

228
00:21:44.638 --> 00:21:45.847
Seasmoke...

229
00:21:48.183 --> 00:21:49.309
<i>Dohaeras!</i>

230
00:21:59.819 --> 00:22:01.196
Do not show fear.

231
00:22:02.989 --> 00:22:04.199
<i>Rybas!</i>

232
00:22:07.160 --> 00:22:08.118
Serve me.

233
00:22:08.119 --> 00:22:09.247
Seasmoke.

234
00:23:20.400 --> 00:23:21.818
I've done it.

235
00:23:29.326 --> 00:23:30.452
No.

236
00:23:44.132 --> 00:23:46.301
They're done! Here!

237
00:23:50.263 --> 00:23:52.474
Mother!

238
00:23:58.897 --> 00:24:01.191
Up. up! Up!

239
00:24:04.903 --> 00:24:05.904
Alyn.

240
00:24:07.072 --> 00:24:08.114
M'lord.

241
00:24:10.325 --> 00:24:14.496
I'm pleased with our progress.
This ship will sail in a few days' time.

242
00:24:15.705 --> 00:24:18.667
The blockade is sure to be challenged.
be it by Lions or Krakens.

243
00:24:19.250 --> 00:24:21.127
Your men will be glad
to have you among them.

244
00:24:21.753 --> 00:24:23.004
I wish you to sail with me.

245
00:24:24.255 --> 00:24:25.423
As my first mate.

246
00:24:26.883 --> 00:24:30.720
- I'm grateful for the offer. m'lord. but...
- You'll set course for Sharp Point.

247
00:24:30.804 --> 00:24:34.599
Lord Bar Emmon wishes to send
his nephew aboard as a boatswain.

248
00:24:34.683 --> 00:24:37.060
There are more experienced men
at your service.

249
00:24:39.020 --> 00:24:42.607
I was younger than you
when I took my first command.

250
00:24:43.900 --> 00:24:46.069
You distinguished yourself
in the Stepstones.

251
00:24:46.152 --> 00:24:48.363
and you have the respect of the crew.

252
00:24:49.948 --> 00:24:52.117
You are a fine choice for this post.

253
00:24:55.787 --> 00:24:57.831
Is this an order or a request?

254
00:25:01.126 --> 00:25:04.796
I will expect you to report
for your duties on the morrow.

255
00:25:06.506 --> 00:25:07.966
As my lordship commands.

256
00:25:30.530 --> 00:25:32.741
- A bit thin. isn't it?
- It's either that or the fish.

257
00:25:32.824 --> 00:25:34.743
Nothing but fish in this damned city.

258
00:25:38.121 --> 00:25:39.414
An ale here.

259
00:25:41.624 --> 00:25:42.959
Aught to eat with it?

260
00:25:43.460 --> 00:25:45.587
I don't think I can stomach it. lass.

261
00:25:45.670 --> 00:25:48.214
Yeah. you've made the right choice there.
I'll tell you that.

262
00:25:51.050 --> 00:25:52.719
Makes you sick. doesn't it?

263
00:25:52.802 --> 00:25:57.348
Knowing they're banqueting every night
at the castle. while we go without.

264
00:25:57.432 --> 00:25:58.600
It can't be true.

265
00:25:58.683 --> 00:26:01.811
My girls were taken to the Red Keep
a few nights ago.

266
00:26:02.645 --> 00:26:06.191
Feasting and merriment
for the new prince regent.

267
00:26:06.274 --> 00:26:09.152
No! And him always acting so correct.

268
00:26:09.235 --> 00:26:11.237
I'll tell you. he's no penny-pincher.

269
00:26:11.821 --> 00:26:14.699
They were well-paid and well-fed too.

270
00:26:14.783 --> 00:26:18.161
Hm. On what?
Fish with more fish on the side?

271
00:26:18.244 --> 00:26:20.580
Racks of lamb. my love.

272
00:26:20.663 --> 00:26:23.875
Mince pies. honey cakes.

273
00:26:23.958 --> 00:26:25.752
Beef and gravy.

274
00:26:25.835 --> 00:26:27.378
And what do you think?

275
00:26:27.462 --> 00:26:31.257
There is to be another revel
on the morrow with dancing.

276
00:26:31.341 --> 00:26:32.509
That ain't right.

277
00:26:33.551 --> 00:26:35.303
Apologies. my good man.

278
00:26:37.180 --> 00:26:39.224
I should not have spoken so free.

279
00:26:39.307 --> 00:26:43.186
The royals would never countenance me
speaking about their bounty.

280
00:26:43.269 --> 00:26:44.395
even if it's true.

281
00:26:45.396 --> 00:26:48.566
King Viserys loved his feasts
and his wine.

282
00:26:49.192 --> 00:26:51.986
but never
while our smallfolk went without.

283
00:26:52.070 --> 00:26:54.697
Mm. aye. But he's gone now.

284
00:26:56.449 --> 00:26:59.369
And his rightful heir denied her seat.

285
00:27:04.249 --> 00:27:08.002
Well. no use wondering
what might have been.

286
00:27:23.476 --> 00:27:25.562
I am far from alone
among your councilors

287
00:27:25.645 --> 00:27:28.189
in holding this to be
a truly unfortunate result. Your Grace.

288
00:27:28.273 --> 00:27:32.735
Seasmoke has fled Dragonstone.
and Ser Steffon was a valiant knight.

289
00:27:32.819 --> 00:27:36.865
Most regrettable. if perhaps foreseeable.

290
00:27:36.948 --> 00:27:38.408
I myself. if you will recall.

291
00:27:38.491 --> 00:27:41.744
was in favor of treating with Lord Mooton
to march on Rook's Rest.

292
00:27:41.828 --> 00:27:46.708
A more conventional approach. true.
Not as sensational.

293
00:27:46.791 --> 00:27:49.127
And. uh. his numbers were few.

294
00:27:49.210 --> 00:27:50.712
But we may yet retake...

295
00:27:53.798 --> 00:27:57.010
It is my fault. I think.
that you have forgotten to fear me.

296
00:28:38.426 --> 00:28:40.845
It was worth the risk.
no matter the outcome.

297
00:28:40.929 --> 00:28:42.388
More good men killed?

298
00:28:43.598 --> 00:28:45.934
- It was my fault.
- Ser Steffon went willingly.

299
00:28:46.017 --> 00:28:47.560
It was a reckless thought.

300
00:28:48.311 --> 00:28:51.397
That an ancient Valyrian beast
would suffer a Darklyn to ride it.

301
00:28:51.481 --> 00:28:53.524
Surely. he was not the only possibility.

302
00:28:53.608 --> 00:28:56.361
Might there not be others among
the highborn of the Seven Kingdoms?

303
00:28:56.444 --> 00:29:00.198
And who will be so foolish as to try
after hearing what befell Ser Steffon?

304
00:29:06.788 --> 00:29:07.997
I will look again.

305
00:29:09.624 --> 00:29:11.668
But Darklyn had the most likely claim.

306
00:29:12.669 --> 00:29:14.170
There is good news to be had.

307
00:29:14.671 --> 00:29:17.340
The smallfolk of King's Landing
are listening.

308
00:29:17.423 --> 00:29:19.175
They were ready enough to hear.

309
00:29:19.258 --> 00:29:21.135
The usurpers have abandoned them.

310
00:29:21.219 --> 00:29:24.055
They are hungry.
and they need someone to blame.

311
00:29:25.807 --> 00:29:28.434
- Will it be enough?
- We have laid the kindling only.

312
00:29:28.518 --> 00:29:31.688
Tonight. we will light it
and watch it begin to flare.

313
00:29:31.771 --> 00:29:34.023
And when it does.
Aemond will put it down with force.

314
00:29:34.107 --> 00:29:38.194
That will make it rise the hotter.
He cannot destroy his own city.

315
00:29:38.277 --> 00:29:40.488
- Neither can they overthrow him.
- Maybe not.

316
00:29:40.571 --> 00:29:45.076
But it is harder to wage war abroad
when you must also keep peace at home.

317
00:29:47.620 --> 00:29:48.913
Then let us see to our plan.

318
00:29:54.627 --> 00:29:56.254
If I may. Your Grace...?

319
00:29:58.089 --> 00:30:00.550
This becomes you.

320
00:30:17.817 --> 00:30:19.068
That's the last one.

321
00:30:20.194 --> 00:30:22.822
- What? They haven't run out. have they?
- Nothing.

322
00:30:23.948 --> 00:30:25.533
There ain't nothing left.

323
00:30:25.616 --> 00:30:27.243
I've been waiting all day.

324
00:30:27.326 --> 00:30:29.370
I'll take anything. Scraps...

325
00:30:38.963 --> 00:30:42.216
Got enough sheep for your dragons. then?
But none for us.

326
00:30:42.300 --> 00:30:43.509
Where's our meat?

327
00:30:44.010 --> 00:30:45.178
We want meat.

328
00:30:49.849 --> 00:30:53.895
<i>It seems. Your Grace.
that the smallfolk have become restless.</i>

329
00:30:53.978 --> 00:30:55.438
So?

330
00:30:55.521 --> 00:30:58.024
There is not food enough in the city.

331
00:30:58.107 --> 00:31:00.943
Those with means
have bought more than their share.

332
00:31:01.027 --> 00:31:03.654
All the more reason
Ser Tyland must break the blockade.

333
00:31:03.738 --> 00:31:08.159
In the meantime. the people are hungry
and their anger is rising.

334
00:31:09.452 --> 00:31:11.329
The enemy without
may be fought with swords.

335
00:31:11.412 --> 00:31:13.706
The enemy within is more insidious.

336
00:31:13.790 --> 00:31:15.583
Why is this anger directed at us?

337
00:31:16.334 --> 00:31:18.795
It is Rhaenyra the Pretender
who ordered the Gullet closed

338
00:31:18.878 --> 00:31:20.421
and left them all to starve.

339
00:31:20.505 --> 00:31:23.049
They still look to you
to ensure their well-being.

340
00:31:24.050 --> 00:31:26.135
That is the burden of authority.

341
00:31:26.761 --> 00:31:28.596
But you should not go it alone.

342
00:31:30.181 --> 00:31:33.392
It does occur to me
that Your Grace has yet to name a Hand.

343
00:31:34.310 --> 00:31:36.187
Ser Criston. of course.
served your brother.

344
00:31:36.270 --> 00:31:40.858
But you need one who may advance
your cause with shrewdness and subtlety.

345
00:31:42.944 --> 00:31:44.695
Do you take me for a fool?

346
00:31:48.324 --> 00:31:49.534
On the contrary. my prince...

347
00:31:49.617 --> 00:31:52.203
I have little patience
for the self-important. Lord Larys.

348
00:31:52.286 --> 00:31:54.664
And even less for flatterers
and lickspittles.

349
00:31:56.290 --> 00:31:57.834
But you are. as it happens. correct.

350
00:31:58.793 --> 00:32:00.211
Every king needs a Hand.

351
00:32:02.421 --> 00:32:04.215
I make it your responsibility.

352
00:32:06.217 --> 00:32:09.345
My prince. it is an honor
I never considered for myself...

353
00:32:09.428 --> 00:32:11.889
No. not to serve as Hand. you toad.

354
00:32:11.973 --> 00:32:13.182
To fetch him.

355
00:32:13.266 --> 00:32:15.143
Send word to Otto Hightower.

356
00:32:15.226 --> 00:32:16.727
My grandsire may be overcautious.

357
00:32:16.811 --> 00:32:19.564
but his devotion to his family
has never been in doubt.

358
00:32:21.399 --> 00:32:23.025
Mm. you'll see it done.

359
00:32:23.109 --> 00:32:24.277
Your Grace.

360
00:32:25.903 --> 00:32:26.861
You're late.

361
00:32:26.863 --> 00:32:30.199
I am happy to report
that His Grace. the king.

362
00:32:30.283 --> 00:32:34.245
has regained consciousness this morning.
if only for a few moments.

363
00:32:34.328 --> 00:32:36.247
You said there was little hope.

364
00:32:36.330 --> 00:32:38.332
He is stronger than I thought.

365
00:32:38.416 --> 00:32:40.710
This morning. his breath comes easier.

366
00:32:40.793 --> 00:32:43.421
He may yet live. thank the gods.

367
00:32:43.963 --> 00:32:45.298
What happy news.

368
00:33:02.648 --> 00:33:04.984
I'll see my brother.

369
00:33:06.277 --> 00:33:07.278
Alone.

370
00:33:30.134 --> 00:33:31.385
What do you remember?

371
00:33:37.266 --> 00:33:38.851
Nothing.

372
00:33:52.281 --> 00:33:53.991
You challenged Meleys.

373
00:33:56.285 --> 00:33:57.370
It was foolish.

374
00:34:01.040 --> 00:34:03.918
I remember nothing.

375
00:34:17.848 --> 00:34:19.183
My prince.

376
00:34:19.267 --> 00:34:21.602
You're in the most capable hands.
Your Grace.

377
00:34:29.652 --> 00:34:32.947
It seems my brother has a long recovery
ahead of him. Grand Maester.

378
00:34:35.741 --> 00:34:38.244
See that he is made to rest comfortably.

379
00:34:43.791 --> 00:34:47.962
<i>And I've decided there is nothing
to be gained with fretfulness.</i>

380
00:34:48.796 --> 00:34:53.092
Not all of us. I suppose.
are called to great deeds.

381
00:34:55.219 --> 00:34:57.471
Some of us must serve in smaller ways.

382
00:34:58.472 --> 00:35:01.350
even if they are not
what we would choose for ourselves.

383
00:35:02.768 --> 00:35:05.146
Oh. meaning no offense. hm?

384
00:35:05.646 --> 00:35:07.273
None of this is your fault.

385
00:35:10.109 --> 00:35:11.235
I want Mother.

386
00:35:13.112 --> 00:35:14.113
Yes.

387
00:35:15.156 --> 00:35:19.118
Well... I know it's difficult. but it...

388
00:36:00.368 --> 00:36:02.078
I bring good news. Rhaena.

389
00:36:02.912 --> 00:36:05.289
Prince Reggio has answered your letter.

390
00:36:05.373 --> 00:36:09.126
He'll be most pleased to shelter
Rhaenyra's youngest sons in Pentos.

391
00:36:10.711 --> 00:36:12.421
And their half-sister.

392
00:36:16.884 --> 00:36:18.302
Thought you'd be happy.

393
00:36:20.388 --> 00:36:22.348
Or at least less morose.

394
00:36:22.431 --> 00:36:23.432
Hm.

395
00:36:23.516 --> 00:36:24.725
You hate it here.

396
00:36:28.270 --> 00:36:30.189
You misled me. my lady.

397
00:36:32.608 --> 00:36:33.609
I did what?

398
00:36:35.903 --> 00:36:38.072
There is a large dragon in the Vale.

399
00:36:43.411 --> 00:36:45.996
Rumor of it began shortly after the war.

400
00:36:46.914 --> 00:36:49.166
Ranging more broadly for food.

401
00:36:49.750 --> 00:36:51.210
my maesters surmise.

402
00:36:55.965 --> 00:36:58.926
It is large and formidable.

403
00:36:59.927 --> 00:37:01.470
But alas. wild.

404
00:37:02.972 --> 00:37:03.973
Alas.

405
00:37:06.600 --> 00:37:10.020
A merchant cog. the <i>Gay Abandon.</i>
will take you to Pentos.

406
00:37:13.399 --> 00:37:15.734
I'll send six good men
to protect you on the crossing.

407
00:37:27.329 --> 00:37:29.039
You know you're not fooling anyone.

408
00:37:31.959 --> 00:37:37.089
Lord Corlys has chosen to raise you up
to serve alongside him.

409
00:37:37.798 --> 00:37:41.135
And yet you still
continue this subterfuge.

410
00:37:41.969 --> 00:37:44.096
Don't want my men to get the wrong idea.

411
00:37:44.180 --> 00:37:45.181
About what?

412
00:37:49.602 --> 00:37:50.853
You're just like him.

413
00:37:52.480 --> 00:37:56.442
- Oh. you make an art of provoking me.
- You saved his life. brother.

414
00:37:56.525 --> 00:37:58.527
Do you never think about
what could be ours?

415
00:37:59.695 --> 00:38:00.905
Or yours. anyway.

416
00:38:02.573 --> 00:38:06.160
The riches. servants...

417
00:38:07.661 --> 00:38:10.039
- the Driftwood Throne.
- We spent the whole of our lives

418
00:38:10.122 --> 00:38:12.791
in the shadow
of the Sea Snake's great castle.

419
00:38:13.334 --> 00:38:15.461
I do not wish to dwell in it any longer.

420
00:38:15.544 --> 00:38:18.672
Hm. And so you belittle
your great opportunity.

421
00:38:19.423 --> 00:38:20.424
While me...

422
00:38:22.176 --> 00:38:23.260
he ignores.

423
00:38:24.178 --> 00:38:25.513
as he always has.

424
00:38:28.390 --> 00:38:34.021
The Sea Snake would sooner have High Tide
claimed by the sea than call us his sons.

425
00:38:35.856 --> 00:38:39.109
Stop wasting your life
waiting for something that'll never come.

426
00:39:04.843 --> 00:39:06.178
It was a bold attempt.

427
00:39:07.054 --> 00:39:08.264
I admire you for it.

428
00:39:12.726 --> 00:39:15.145
They say you struck Lord Bartimos today.

429
00:39:15.980 --> 00:39:17.815
In view of the staff and guard.

430
00:39:19.233 --> 00:39:21.110
The household is abuzz with it.

431
00:39:23.070 --> 00:39:25.030
He is lucky
I did not have his tongue.

432
00:39:26.031 --> 00:39:30.160
And what did he say
that was so deserving?

433
00:39:33.747 --> 00:39:37.209
I have tired of being protected.
Jace.

434
00:39:40.170 --> 00:39:41.128
Hm.

435
00:39:41.130 --> 00:39:44.508
I bring to mind too much
their mothers or their daughters.

436
00:39:45.968 --> 00:39:47.469
They must see in me a ruler.

437
00:39:48.304 --> 00:39:50.639
And the symbols of authority
are not jewels and gowns.

438
00:39:50.723 --> 00:39:52.266
but the shield and the sword.

439
00:39:52.349 --> 00:39:54.226
My ruler is my mother.

440
00:39:55.311 --> 00:39:56.937
And I do not wish it otherwise.

441
00:40:00.441 --> 00:40:02.109
Will you lead us to war yourself?

442
00:40:02.192 --> 00:40:04.445
For a certainty. I cannot remain here.
pacing the floors.

443
00:40:04.528 --> 00:40:06.322
waiting for defeat and despair
to visit me.

444
00:40:06.405 --> 00:40:08.949
- Oh. don't be ridiculous.
- I'm doing all I can.

445
00:40:09.033 --> 00:40:11.285
I have directed Lord Mooton
to march on Rook's Rest

446
00:40:11.368 --> 00:40:13.621
and sent another raven
to the Vale to persuade...

447
00:40:13.704 --> 00:40:18.000
We may marshal the strength of the Vale.
Maidenpool. and all our allies besides.

448
00:40:18.626 --> 00:40:21.503
We will still never match
the strength of the Green armies.

449
00:40:22.880 --> 00:40:25.883
We need Daemon. And his dragon.

450
00:40:26.550 --> 00:40:27.968
May I be free for even one hour

451
00:40:28.052 --> 00:40:30.262
of the constant refrain
of Daemon. Daemon. Daemon?

452
00:40:30.346 --> 00:40:31.680
Your Grace.

453
00:40:32.556 --> 00:40:33.849
The lady Mysaria.

454
00:40:36.143 --> 00:40:39.188
My queen. our gift is sent.

455
00:40:43.067 --> 00:40:44.151
What gift?

456
00:40:45.778 --> 00:40:48.197
Let us hope for clouds
over the Blackwater tonight.

457
00:43:09.838 --> 00:43:11.298
You said he'd improved.

458
00:43:13.467 --> 00:43:17.012
His Grace sleeps nine hours of every ten.

459
00:43:17.679 --> 00:43:21.558
but he did open his eyes and speak.
however briefly.

460
00:43:21.642 --> 00:43:24.102
His mending may be long and painful.

461
00:43:24.186 --> 00:43:28.273
but it is my sincere hope
that His Grace will be spared.

462
00:43:28.816 --> 00:43:30.359
And what will he be if he lives?

463
00:43:40.244 --> 00:43:43.622
My letters to my father.

464
00:43:45.707 --> 00:43:50.212
I have sent ravens again
to Highgarden and to Oldtown.

465
00:43:50.796 --> 00:43:53.298
And now to all the great houses
in the Reach.

466
00:43:54.258 --> 00:43:57.427
There has been no word
from Ser Otto. as of yet.

467
00:44:03.559 --> 00:44:06.645
There is war in the Reach now. Your Grace.

468
00:44:06.728 --> 00:44:10.524
House Beesbury has raised arms
against the Hightower host.

469
00:44:10.607 --> 00:44:14.152
Retribution for their lord's demise.

470
00:44:42.097 --> 00:44:43.098
I'm sorry.

471
00:44:45.142 --> 00:44:46.268
I'm sorry.

472
00:45:26.433 --> 00:45:27.559
Sister.

473
00:45:28.185 --> 00:45:29.185
Gwayne.

474
00:45:31.021 --> 00:45:32.356
It is well that I found you.

475
00:45:33.607 --> 00:45:35.442
I wish to give you my blessing.

476
00:45:36.610 --> 00:45:40.739
Well. my thanks to the queen dowager.

477
00:45:46.662 --> 00:45:48.455
I wondered if you'd heard from Father.

478
00:45:49.247 --> 00:45:52.668
I've sent ravens to Highgarden
and Oldtown. but have had no reply.

479
00:45:53.377 --> 00:45:56.797
I've heard nothing.
But neither have I sent any message.

480
00:45:57.422 --> 00:46:01.218
If he wrote letters. it would be to you.
You were always his favorite.

481
00:46:02.678 --> 00:46:07.224
- Strange there has been no word.
- Otto Hightower is ever-resourceful.

482
00:46:08.100 --> 00:46:10.102
He will send news
when there is news to send.

483
00:46:13.897 --> 00:46:17.275
I often wonder what life could have been
if he had brought you to court instead.

484
00:46:20.487 --> 00:46:23.824
I'm the eldest son. It was right
that I was raised at Oldtown.

485
00:46:23.907 --> 00:46:26.868
You were 8 years of age and motherless.
It must have been difficult.

486
00:46:27.411 --> 00:46:29.204
You get on with it. don't you?

487
00:46:30.372 --> 00:46:32.666
When there isn't any choice.

488
00:46:36.670 --> 00:46:37.921
My son. Daeron.

489
00:46:40.924 --> 00:46:42.175
What's he like?

490
00:46:43.468 --> 00:46:45.178
Does he not write to you?

491
00:46:45.262 --> 00:46:46.763
Less and less these days.

492
00:46:49.433 --> 00:46:51.018
Ten-and-six now.

493
00:46:52.561 --> 00:46:55.063
Letters perhaps hold less of his interest.

494
00:47:00.152 --> 00:47:01.445
He's stalwart.

495
00:47:02.904 --> 00:47:03.947
Clever.

496
00:47:04.031 --> 00:47:06.825
As adept with his lute
as he is with his sword.

497
00:47:08.660 --> 00:47:12.080
And a feature in the fancies
of many a young lady. I'll wager.

498
00:47:16.918 --> 00:47:18.211
He's kind.

499
00:47:22.049 --> 00:47:23.133
That's good.

500
00:47:25.844 --> 00:47:28.847
Kindness is a quality
I've found lacking in his brothers.

501
00:47:28.930 --> 00:47:29.931
Mm.

502
00:47:30.432 --> 00:47:32.601
You did well to send him to ward.

503
00:47:33.268 --> 00:47:36.772
As it seems. the Red Keep.
for all its privileges.

504
00:47:36.855 --> 00:47:40.484
may. in fact. be a less
than salubrious environment

505
00:47:40.567 --> 00:47:42.110
for the forming of young men.

506
00:47:43.737 --> 00:47:45.614
Was it the court or was it their mother?

507
00:47:48.700 --> 00:47:50.410
I'm sure you did your best.

508
00:47:56.708 --> 00:47:58.627
I must join Ser Criston.

509
00:48:00.003 --> 00:48:01.421
Wish us luck. sister.

510
00:48:03.006 --> 00:48:05.175
I shall pray to the Warrior
for your safe return.

511
00:48:08.178 --> 00:48:09.221
Well...

512
00:48:10.555 --> 00:48:11.556
Farewell.

513
00:48:53.807 --> 00:48:54.975
Your Grace.

514
00:48:58.353 --> 00:49:00.105
This one's stopped singing.

515
00:49:01.273 --> 00:49:02.774
Isn't that strange?

516
00:49:05.527 --> 00:49:07.237
I thought we might light a candle.

517
00:49:08.822 --> 00:49:09.865
For Aegon...

518
00:49:11.700 --> 00:49:13.076
and all our lost souls.

519
00:49:45.317 --> 00:49:46.735
Where'd you get that food?

520
00:49:46.818 --> 00:49:48.195
- Rhaenyra's ships.
- Ships?

521
00:49:48.278 --> 00:49:51.114
They came ashore in the middle
of the night with gifts from the queen.

522
00:49:51.198 --> 00:49:52.782
She thinks of us even now!

523
00:50:07.797 --> 00:50:09.090
Give me that!

524
00:50:10.258 --> 00:50:12.135
- It's mine!
- Give it to me!

525
00:50:17.641 --> 00:50:18.850
Out of the way!

526
00:50:38.995 --> 00:50:42.832
Your Graces. we must leave. Now.

527
00:50:48.505 --> 00:50:50.465
Get the queens to the wheelhouse!

528
00:50:54.427 --> 00:50:56.930
Mind your flanks. Protect your corners.

529
00:50:58.932 --> 00:51:01.184
Keep moving. This way. Your Grace.

530
00:51:04.104 --> 00:51:05.814
It's the queen of fishes!

531
00:51:07.649 --> 00:51:08.984
Keep moving!

532
00:51:09.609 --> 00:51:11.987
Long live Queen Rhaenyra!

533
00:51:13.071 --> 00:51:15.615
- Get to the wheelhouse!
- Long live Queen Rhaenyra!

534
00:51:15.699 --> 00:51:17.450
Helaena!

535
00:51:17.534 --> 00:51:18.535
Your Grace!

536
00:51:19.828 --> 00:51:21.204
- This way. Your Grace.
- My queen!

537
00:51:21.288 --> 00:51:23.832
- Get off!
- No. No!

538
00:51:25.250 --> 00:51:26.918
Sheathe your swords!

539
00:51:28.628 --> 00:51:30.130
Sheathe your swords!

540
00:51:30.213 --> 00:51:32.465
Back away!

541
00:51:32.549 --> 00:51:34.050
You heard the queen!

542
00:51:34.134 --> 00:51:35.593
Sheathe those swords!

543
00:51:43.560 --> 00:51:45.312
- No!
- Get back!

544
00:51:45.395 --> 00:51:46.938
- Out of the way!
- Back!

545
00:51:47.022 --> 00:51:49.107
- Get back!
- Go. Helaena! Go!

546
00:51:49.190 --> 00:51:51.318
Out of my way! Out of my way!

547
00:51:56.364 --> 00:51:57.365
Come on!

548
00:52:01.119 --> 00:52:03.788
My queens. this way! Inside!

549
00:52:17.761 --> 00:52:20.555
- Long live Queen Rhaenyra!
- Queen Rhaenyra!

550
00:52:21.806 --> 00:52:24.392
Long live Queen Rhaenyra!

551
00:52:26.644 --> 00:52:28.396
Run them down if you must.

552
00:52:30.106 --> 00:52:32.442
Ride! Ride!

553
00:53:09.270 --> 00:53:10.313
No more.

554
00:53:11.147 --> 00:53:13.233
My lord. Only...

555
00:53:13.316 --> 00:53:14.943
...the Grand Maester instructed me to.

556
00:53:15.026 --> 00:53:18.530
The king will be most eager
for his draft in an hour.

557
00:53:31.459 --> 00:53:33.545
The drink takes the pain away.

558
00:53:34.170 --> 00:53:35.672
but it dulls your mind.

559
00:53:37.549 --> 00:53:40.385
Take heart. Your Grace. You've already
written yourself into legend.

560
00:53:40.468 --> 00:53:42.011
You survived dragonfire.

561
00:53:45.515 --> 00:53:47.392
But I'm afraid you will never be whole.

562
00:53:48.935 --> 00:53:51.312
Orwyle has exhausted his abilities.

563
00:53:52.605 --> 00:53:54.065
He's bound your leg...

564
00:53:56.192 --> 00:53:58.194
but you will never run again.

565
00:53:59.946 --> 00:54:00.947
Your mind

566
00:54:01.906 --> 00:54:03.783
is all that remains to you.

567
00:54:03.867 --> 00:54:05.368
I do not say that gladly.

568
00:54:09.831 --> 00:54:11.666
I came screaming into the world

569
00:54:11.749 --> 00:54:14.419
in the bowels
of one of Harren's great towers.

570
00:54:16.546 --> 00:54:21.259
My lungs were strong.
but my foot so twisted that...

571
00:54:22.886 --> 00:54:25.472
my father named it sorcery...

572
00:54:27.307 --> 00:54:30.101
accusing a member
of our household of casting

573
00:54:31.019 --> 00:54:32.729
malign spells.

574
00:54:35.732 --> 00:54:36.733
Well...

575
00:54:37.942 --> 00:54:39.319
People will pity you.

576
00:54:40.195 --> 00:54:43.740
Either behind your back
or in your presence.

577
00:54:46.409 --> 00:54:47.827
And they will stare.

578
00:54:50.288 --> 00:54:51.873
At you. at your...

579
00:54:55.001 --> 00:54:56.252
Or turn away.

580
00:55:00.048 --> 00:55:02.008
And they will underestimate you.

581
00:55:04.552 --> 00:55:06.596
And this will be your advantage.

582
00:55:06.679 --> 00:55:08.806
No. N... No.

583
00:55:15.730 --> 00:55:20.276
Your brother rules in your place now.
which means that your life is in danger.

584
00:55:22.654 --> 00:55:24.822
But I think you know that.

585
00:55:29.452 --> 00:55:30.453
Help me.

586
00:55:32.997 --> 00:55:33.998
Please.

587
00:56:16.499 --> 00:56:17.500
Brother.

588
00:56:20.420 --> 00:56:22.171
Daemon. she's gone.

589
00:56:35.602 --> 00:56:36.728
I'm sorry.

590
00:56:43.192 --> 00:56:44.527
You needed me.

591
00:56:47.405 --> 00:56:48.448
I'm here now.

592
00:56:58.583 --> 00:56:59.584
I'm here now.

593
00:57:05.632 --> 00:57:07.008
Your Grace.

594
00:57:10.136 --> 00:57:13.556
Sorrowful news from Riverrun. my king.

595
00:57:14.849 --> 00:57:16.351
Lord Grover is dead.

596
00:57:19.062 --> 00:57:20.146
Uh...

597
00:57:21.147 --> 00:57:23.232
- The old man.
- Indeed.

598
00:57:24.442 --> 00:57:28.738
Young Oscar Tully is now
Lord Paramount of the Riverlands.

599
00:57:31.407 --> 00:57:33.660
What was the manner
of Lord Grover's passing?

600
00:57:33.743 --> 00:57:35.203
Well. he'd been ill. of course.

601
00:57:35.286 --> 00:57:36.286
Mm-hm.

602
00:57:37.121 --> 00:57:41.209
Riverrun's maesters...
have been at their wits' end.

603
00:57:41.918 --> 00:57:47.340
Our own healer. Alys Rivers.
volunteered her renowned skills.

604
00:57:47.423 --> 00:57:49.217
She plied her craft. but...

605
00:57:51.427 --> 00:57:53.012
there was naught more to be done.

606
00:58:31.342 --> 00:58:32.385
Hey. look!

607
00:58:34.679 --> 00:58:36.347
- Get inside!
- Let's go!

608
00:58:36.431 --> 00:58:38.015
Quick! Hurry!

609
00:58:38.558 --> 00:58:39.934
Ah. ahh!

610
01:00:11.234 --> 01:00:14.529
Your banners were carried
from the ship into the city.

611
01:00:14.612 --> 01:00:16.781
They went as far
as the gates of the Red Keep

612
01:00:16.864 --> 01:00:18.157
before they were turned away.

613
01:00:18.241 --> 01:00:20.326
It is as we hoped.
a warning to the usurpers

614
01:00:20.409 --> 01:00:23.079
that you have strength
beyond what they have credited.

615
01:00:25.331 --> 01:00:27.124
I thought you'd be pleased.

616
01:00:29.210 --> 01:00:31.212
I do not think I can win this war.

617
01:00:33.548 --> 01:00:34.882
I think you are tired.

618
01:00:34.966 --> 01:00:37.718
My own son questions my capabilities.

619
01:00:40.221 --> 01:00:42.348
He thinks I need Daemon at my side.

620
01:00:44.517 --> 01:00:45.810
And Daemon himself...

621
01:00:45.893 --> 01:00:48.938
He has ever done what suits Daemon.

622
01:00:53.860 --> 01:00:55.820
He was everything I wanted to be.

623
01:00:57.321 --> 01:00:58.321
Carefree.

624
01:00:59.657 --> 01:01:00.657
And dangerous.

625
01:01:02.743 --> 01:01:03.828
A man.

626
01:01:05.079 --> 01:01:06.706
And I was what he wanted.

627
01:01:07.665 --> 01:01:11.002
Cherished by my father
and made my father's heir.

628
01:01:11.085 --> 01:01:12.628
We were halves of a whole.

629
01:01:16.048 --> 01:01:17.884
But he's never been at peace.

630
01:01:20.636 --> 01:01:23.681
He wished to possess me.
but not to be possessed.

631
01:01:23.764 --> 01:01:27.393
And to see me take hold. finally.
of what he'd always believed to be his.

632
01:01:30.646 --> 01:01:32.315
I fear what he may now do.

633
01:01:39.155 --> 01:01:43.409
- I fear he may have turned against me.
- It is more his way to disappear.

634
01:01:43.492 --> 01:01:45.202
In either case. I have lost him.

635
01:01:46.746 --> 01:01:48.289
And Caraxes with him.

636
01:01:49.290 --> 01:01:52.960
Rhaenys and her dragon are dead.
I have Syrax and two young beasts.

637
01:01:53.044 --> 01:01:54.629
We cannot take on Vhagar alone.

638
01:01:55.296 --> 01:01:56.380
And I have no army.

639
01:01:56.464 --> 01:01:59.717
You have the Velaryon fleet
and the men who fight in it.

640
01:02:01.010 --> 01:02:02.094
It's not enough.

641
01:02:03.763 --> 01:02:06.557
And even if we somehow prevailed.

642
01:02:06.641 --> 01:02:09.310
how will I rule a kingdom
when my own son doubts me?

643
01:02:10.478 --> 01:02:11.479
You have me.

644
01:02:14.357 --> 01:02:15.608
You have my thanks.

645
01:02:16.651 --> 01:02:17.735
Truly.

646
01:02:30.247 --> 01:02:31.999
It was my father.

647
01:02:38.297 --> 01:02:39.924
I was still a child.

648
01:02:40.549 --> 01:02:44.095
He had his pleasure with me.

649
01:02:45.137 --> 01:02:46.931
And when. after many months of this.

650
01:02:47.014 --> 01:02:51.394
it became evident
that his seed had taken root...

651
01:02:59.360 --> 01:03:01.237
There is a scar here as well.

652
01:03:03.322 --> 01:03:05.449
I cannot bear children.

653
01:03:07.493 --> 01:03:08.995
He left me for dead.

654
01:03:10.538 --> 01:03:11.706
But I lived.

655
01:03:11.789 --> 01:03:13.332
I'm so sorry.

656
01:03:13.416 --> 01:03:15.793
I swore to myself
I would never trust another.

657
01:03:15.876 --> 01:03:18.963
And that oath has stood me well.

658
01:03:20.047 --> 01:03:22.508
This world is cold and cruel.

659
01:03:22.591 --> 01:03:25.594
and there are few in it who are steadfast.

660
01:03:26.262 --> 01:03:30.307
You. I think. are steadfast.

661
01:03:31.017 --> 01:03:34.437
You have seen me as worthy.
as an equal even.

662
01:03:35.896 --> 01:03:38.107
Because of that. I will serve you.

663
01:03:38.899 --> 01:03:41.277
I believe you are meant to be queen.

664
01:04:53.224 --> 01:04:55.601
Begging your pardon. Your Grace.

665
01:04:56.936 --> 01:05:00.397
The dragon Seasmoke has been
sighted flying over Spicetown.

666
01:05:00.481 --> 01:05:01.690
Yes. he does that.

667
01:05:02.525 --> 01:05:05.444
From what we have heard.
he has a rider.

668
01:05:06.445 --> 01:05:09.281
- Who?
- Impossible to tell from the ground.

669
01:05:10.366 --> 01:05:12.868
- The Greens?
- I don't know who else it could be.

670
01:05:13.661 --> 01:05:14.870
Shall I summon your council?

671
01:05:36.267 --> 01:05:37.268
Mother!
